WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.669 --> 00:00:06.697
<i>Carroll was convicted in 2004 for
the murders of 14 young women.</i>

2
00:00:06.874 --> 00:00:09.673
<i>We need you in Virginia. Ryan.</i>
RYAN: I'm not an agent anymore.

3
00:00:09.843 --> 00:00:12.472
You caught Carroll. No
one knows him like you do.

4
00:00:12.679 --> 00:00:16.081
- So. what's my sequel about. Joe?
- We're gonna write this together. Ryan.

5
00:00:17.784 --> 00:00:24.349
Even though you slept with my wife. I
have so many surprises waiting for you.

6
00:00:24.591 --> 00:00:28.050
He fancies himself Edgar Allan Poe.
That was the impetus for his novel.

7
00:00:28.228 --> 00:00:31.221
- We got more bodies.
- He removed the eyes. Carroll's signature.

8
00:00:31.498 --> 00:00:34.696
He used this prison guard to gain
access to the Internet to create a cult.

9
00:00:35.402 --> 00:00:38.861
- Agent Parker's taking the lead.
- Cults. My specialty.

10
00:00:39.072 --> 00:00:41.598
Ice pick lady. Gay
neighbors. The nanny.

11
00:00:42.509 --> 00:00:44.444
How do they figure
into your new plot?

12
00:00:44.678 --> 00:00:46.909
Where is he? Joey?
Where's my son?

13
00:00:47.080 --> 00:00:49.845
- Carroll knows where the kid is.
- He's not gonna tell us.

14
00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:51.348
Might tell his wife.

15
00:00:52.085 --> 00:00:55.317
You son of a bitch.
Where's my son?

16
00:00:56.823 --> 00:00:58.815
<i>"Take thy beak
from out of my heart</i>

17
00:00:59.026 --> 00:01:01.928
<i>And take thy form
from off my door!"</i>

18
00:01:02.129 --> 00:01:05.395
<i>Quoth the raven. "Nevermore."</i>

19
00:01:05.599 --> 00:01:07.431
<i>And the raven never flitting</i>

20
00:01:07.634 --> 00:01:09.694
<i>Still is sitting.
still is sitting</i>

21
00:01:09.903 --> 00:01:13.135
If you don't like the piece.
call my editor. scream at him.

22
00:01:13.373 --> 00:01:17.743
It is too early for this
crap. You have a nice day.

23
00:01:17.945 --> 00:01:22.315
<i>That lies floating on the floor
Shall be lifted - nevermore!</i>

24
00:01:44.538 --> 00:01:47.235
Whoa. What the hell? Hey.

25
00:02:11.498 --> 00:02:12.522
Good morning. Claire.

26
00:02:24.945 --> 00:02:27.210
- Good morning. ma'am.
- Is Ryan Hardy here?

27
00:02:27.414 --> 00:02:30.145
No. ma'am. he left
over an hour ago.

28
00:02:44.231 --> 00:02:48.066
How'd you sleep? The motel they
stuck us in sucks. The bed is bricks.

29
00:02:48.235 --> 00:02:50.966
- How many fingerprints?
- Nine. in total.

30
00:02:51.138 --> 00:02:54.131
Several were older prints.
but upstairs in the attic room...

31
00:02:54.574 --> 00:02:56.475
that is where we found six sets.

32
00:02:56.677 --> 00:03:00.546
They're the newest ones we found. I'm
guessing that's where they gathered most.

33
00:03:01.148 --> 00:03:04.550
Four of the sets belong to
Emma. Jacob. Paul and Jordy.

34
00:03:04.751 --> 00:03:08.244
Yeah. That's four. And the guy
with the Poe mask that attacked me.

35
00:03:08.455 --> 00:03:10.185
- Five.
- You really think this cult...

36
00:03:10.357 --> 00:03:12.326
is limited to six people?

37
00:03:13.326 --> 00:03:16.262
We weren't supposed to
find their little clubhouse.

38
00:03:16.496 --> 00:03:19.933
I tell you. there's gotta be something
here to tell us where Joey Matthews is.

39
00:03:20.100 --> 00:03:22.626
Mm-mm. I've been
through every piece.

40
00:03:22.803 --> 00:03:24.897
Nothing points to where
he is or why they took him.

41
00:03:25.372 --> 00:03:29.104
I don't understand what this cult is
about. I mean. what's Carroll's message?

42
00:03:29.342 --> 00:03:33.006
Koresh. Jones. Manson all used
mind control to reinforce their message...

43
00:03:33.180 --> 00:03:34.910
of unity over the individual.

44
00:03:35.115 --> 00:03:37.846
Didn't Manson convince his
family to kill for his means?

45
00:03:38.018 --> 00:03:40.578
Yeah. but he dressed it up
in several motives at once.

46
00:03:41.021 --> 00:03:45.391
He'd test his followers with acts of
murder in order to prove their devotion.

47
00:03:45.592 --> 00:03:49.222
He's a brilliant manipulator.
Get anyone to do anything.

48
00:03:50.797 --> 00:03:55.292
Joe was a teacher. He was a man
of ideas. And he was brilliant at it.

49
00:03:55.802 --> 00:04:00.035
I witnessed him in class. He could
engage and inspire his students...

50
00:04:00.207 --> 00:04:02.438
in ways that I had
never seen before.

51
00:04:03.810 --> 00:04:07.372
Hester had broken
free from all of that.

52
00:04:07.547 --> 00:04:11.541
She had created
her own moral code.

53
00:04:12.586 --> 00:04:18.958
Are we not able to break
free and do whatever we want?

54
00:04:19.893 --> 00:04:23.330
As long as we are willing
to pay life's consequences.

55
00:04:24.765 --> 00:04:27.826
What is your moral code?

56
00:04:29.436 --> 00:04:33.168
Make it unique unto yourself...

57
00:04:33.340 --> 00:04:37.072
and it will bleed
into your writing.

58
00:04:40.213 --> 00:04:41.806
Yeah.

59
00:04:41.982 --> 00:04:43.177
Thank you.

60
00:04:43.984 --> 00:04:46.112
How's your bedside
manner? Jordy's awake.

61
00:04:48.021 --> 00:04:50.115
Hey. Jordy. How you feeling?

62
00:04:50.323 --> 00:04:51.814
How am I feeling? You shot me.

63
00:04:52.058 --> 00:04:53.822
Yeah. I'm sorry about that.

64
00:04:54.060 --> 00:04:55.824
Tell us where Joey Matthews is.

65
00:04:57.297 --> 00:04:59.027
Oh. is that all?

66
00:04:59.199 --> 00:05:01.361
Do you think I'm stupid?

67
00:05:01.568 --> 00:05:02.592
I'm not talking.

68
00:05:02.803 --> 00:05:07.002
- I think you're looking at the death penalty.
- I'll never make it to the chair.

69
00:05:07.207 --> 00:05:10.666
I'm a correctional officer. I
won't last a week in prison.

70
00:05:11.945 --> 00:05:13.811
But can I tell
you a little secret?

71
00:05:15.715 --> 00:05:17.013
It was worth it.

72
00:05:17.984 --> 00:05:23.013
To kill those girls. To hold
them in my hands when they died.

73
00:05:23.456 --> 00:05:26.358
- I felt their last breath.
- You know I talked to Joe. right?

74
00:05:27.460 --> 00:05:31.488
He was very upset to find out that
you were still alive. He wanted you dead.

75
00:05:31.698 --> 00:05:35.794
You failed. You were supposed to kill
Claire Matthews. Weren't those the rules?

76
00:05:37.904 --> 00:05:41.705
I know what you're doing.
It's not going to work.

77
00:05:41.908 --> 00:05:44.503
Come on. Jordy. Where's Joey?

78
00:05:47.013 --> 00:05:49.744
La. la. la. I can't hear you.

79
00:05:49.916 --> 00:05:52.249
<i>Look at what's happened to me</i>

80
00:05:52.419 --> 00:05:55.583
Come on. Just tell us
where... Just tell us...

81
00:05:55.755 --> 00:05:57.223
<i>Suddenly I'm up
on top of the world</i>

82
00:05:57.390 --> 00:05:59.518
Jordy. Jordy.

83
00:05:59.693 --> 00:06:01.662
<i>Should've been somebody else</i>

84
00:06:01.828 --> 00:06:03.524
Aah! PARKER: Hey.

85
00:06:03.697 --> 00:06:05.529
- Sorry. I slipped.
- You can't do that.

86
00:06:06.900 --> 00:06:10.860
You can't do that.
Hey. Hey. No. no...

87
00:06:11.071 --> 00:06:13.438
Sorry for the shaky
cam. It's from a cell.

88
00:06:13.607 --> 00:06:14.631
What are we watching?

89
00:06:14.808 --> 00:06:18.006
Street performance by a man dressed
as Poe this morning. Recognize the mask?

90
00:06:18.178 --> 00:06:22.240
- He was doing this on the street?
- It's very common. It's the historical district.

91
00:06:22.449 --> 00:06:23.576
Here it comes.

92
00:06:27.454 --> 00:06:29.719
Hey. wait. Who's the victim?

93
00:06:29.923 --> 00:06:31.789
Stan Fellows. Book critic.

94
00:06:32.025 --> 00:06:35.359
Yeah. Richmond paper. I know this
guy. I interviewed him for my book.

95
00:06:35.562 --> 00:06:39.966
He wrote a scathing review of Carroll's
book. <i>The Gothic Sea</i>. The worst I read.

96
00:06:40.166 --> 00:06:43.034
Suspect threw confetti on
the crowd. It's got writing on it.

97
00:06:43.203 --> 00:06:47.197
<i>"Generous critic fanned the poet's fire.
Taught the world with reason to admire."</i>

98
00:06:47.374 --> 00:06:48.535
That's Poe.

99
00:06:48.742 --> 00:06:51.906
So Carroll wants his followers
to exact revenge on his critics?

100
00:06:52.078 --> 00:06:53.444
That could take a while.

101
00:06:53.680 --> 00:06:57.242
<i>The recent string of murders in the
wake of Joe Carroll's prison escape...</i>

102
00:06:57.417 --> 00:07:01.548
<i>is raising all kinds of speculation.
Is this the work of a cult?</i>

103
00:07:01.755 --> 00:07:05.817
<i>- Authorities refuse to comment...</i>
- The press is officially calling us a cult.

104
00:07:05.992 --> 00:07:08.894
The FBI won't confirm it so they've
issued a media blackout. Heh.

105
00:07:09.095 --> 00:07:12.429
That's because they're completely
clueless. Have you talked to Emma?

106
00:07:12.632 --> 00:07:16.797
- No. No. why?
- Things are weird between you guys.

107
00:07:17.003 --> 00:07:21.304
And to be fair. you haven't
been that nice to her.

108
00:07:22.909 --> 00:07:25.743
- Is that Rick? Heh. Awesome.
- He's everywhere today.

109
00:07:25.946 --> 00:07:28.006
Look. here's some
cool footage of the fire.

110
00:07:29.449 --> 00:07:34.012
So Torch Man is a hit.
huh? I knew it would work.

111
00:07:34.921 --> 00:07:37.948
If you hate blood so much.
what about fire? It's flashy.

112
00:07:38.124 --> 00:07:42.824
- I don't hate blood.
- What about removing the eyes?

113
00:07:42.996 --> 00:07:47.161
- You can't do that with fire.
- Actually. you can. doofus.

114
00:07:47.367 --> 00:07:50.633
What Jordy means is. the
eyes are Joe's signature.

115
00:07:50.837 --> 00:07:54.001
And fire doesn't go with gouging eyes.
- You're being literal.

116
00:07:54.240 --> 00:07:58.439
Besides. we're supposed to find our
own voice. Not just copy Joe's story.

117
00:07:58.645 --> 00:08:00.375
Doofus <i>deux.</i>

118
00:08:00.613 --> 00:08:01.808
But I like Joe's story.

119
00:08:01.982 --> 00:08:05.111
Then have at it. Jordy. You
do it your way. I'll do it mine.

120
00:08:09.389 --> 00:08:12.553
- Just talk to Emma. okay?
- You don't see it. do you?

121
00:08:12.792 --> 00:08:15.455
I mean. that girl
wears a lot of faces.

122
00:08:16.262 --> 00:08:19.289
And I don't get the Emma you get.
- What Emma is that. Paul?

123
00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:23.770
- Oh. we were just talking...
- Don't cover for him.

124
00:08:23.970 --> 00:08:26.166
He has something to say.

125
00:08:29.209 --> 00:08:30.905
Forget it.

126
00:08:42.922 --> 00:08:47.383
Got him. It's a business owner downtown
with a security camera two blocks away.

127
00:08:47.594 --> 00:08:50.189
- Did you get a license plate?
- Way ahead.

128
00:08:50.397 --> 00:08:54.994
Car is registered to Rick
Kester. he's 29.120 Church Hill.

129
00:09:19.859 --> 00:09:21.623
This room's clear.

130
00:09:22.128 --> 00:09:23.824
Clear. PARKER: Hey.

131
00:09:46.219 --> 00:09:48.916
- Please don't hurt me. PARKER:
We're not gonna hurt you.

132
00:09:49.122 --> 00:09:51.648
- Who are you?
- Maggie Kester. I live here.

133
00:09:51.858 --> 00:09:54.623
- You know Rick Kester?
- Yes. I do. He's my husband.

134
00:10:01.534 --> 00:10:03.400
Thank you for
agreeing to talk to us.

135
00:10:03.603 --> 00:10:05.572
I don't wanna stay
in that house alone.

136
00:10:05.772 --> 00:10:12.269
- When'd you last hear from your husband?
- Last night. He called. I didn't pick up.

137
00:10:13.713 --> 00:10:17.650
We're separated. Six months now.

138
00:10:18.218 --> 00:10:20.187
Um...

139
00:10:20.854 --> 00:10:23.722
Seven-fifteen. He
didn't leave a message.

140
00:10:24.390 --> 00:10:27.360
- Why were you hiding from us?
- I didn't know it was you. I was scared.

141
00:10:29.095 --> 00:10:34.295
He still has a key. He's been bothering
me and calling me. showing up at work.

142
00:10:34.601 --> 00:10:39.437
Rick can be scary
when he wants to be.

143
00:10:39.639 --> 00:10:43.098
We pulled your records
and your story checks out.

144
00:10:43.276 --> 00:10:48.237
But I'm curious about this
police report that you filled out...

145
00:10:48.448 --> 00:10:51.748
couple years back in
the emergency room.

146
00:10:53.086 --> 00:10:55.146
Why did your
husband try to kill you?

147
00:10:59.392 --> 00:11:03.625
- Ah. I asked him for a divorce.
- So he took a knife to you?

148
00:11:21.514 --> 00:11:26.043
They never pressed charges. I
wouldn't testify because he was sorry.

149
00:11:26.219 --> 00:11:30.680
- He was. He wasn't always like this.
- When did you notice a change?

150
00:11:30.857 --> 00:11:33.622
He lost his job and
had all this free time...

151
00:11:33.793 --> 00:11:37.787
- and started hanging out with new friends.
- Did you meet any of them?

152
00:11:37.997 --> 00:11:41.798
No. I didn't want anything to do with
them. He'd come home with weird ideas...

153
00:11:41.968 --> 00:11:44.403
- and saying crazy things.
- What things?

154
00:11:44.571 --> 00:11:48.736
He started talking a lot about
death and how life didn't matter.

155
00:11:48.975 --> 00:11:51.069
He got really dark.
He was depressed.

156
00:11:56.516 --> 00:12:01.318
We're going to give you protection
until we find your husband. Excuse me.

157
00:12:06.960 --> 00:12:07.984
So you believe her?

158
00:12:08.194 --> 00:12:11.494
Yeah. I do. She's tragic and
pathetic and I know her well.

159
00:12:12.065 --> 00:12:14.364
- How so?
- She wants the man in her head...

160
00:12:14.534 --> 00:12:18.494
not the one she married. She's my
mother. my sister. my other sister.

161
00:12:18.671 --> 00:12:20.902
No one ever wants to
see what's really there.

162
00:12:21.541 --> 00:12:24.978
We need to find the husband.
He's the closest thing to finding Joey.

163
00:12:25.678 --> 00:12:27.998
Why don't you let me see
Joe? See if I can get him to talk.

164
00:12:28.381 --> 00:12:31.545
Let me try. I think it's
time Joe and I met anyway.

165
00:12:43.029 --> 00:12:44.258
What do you want. Paul?

166
00:12:45.765 --> 00:12:46.858
Do you need any help?

167
00:12:47.734 --> 00:12:48.758
No.

168
00:12:51.237 --> 00:12:55.902
Look. I'm sorry about before
and whatever I've done.

169
00:12:56.276 --> 00:12:59.769
But we're all in this together and
I don't want things to be like this.

170
00:13:00.913 --> 00:13:03.382
- I don't either. Paul.
- Can we sort of pretend...

171
00:13:03.816 --> 00:13:07.947
that we like each other
and see where that goes?

172
00:13:12.058 --> 00:13:13.720
Truce.

173
00:13:18.364 --> 00:13:21.027
- Bitch.
- Don't try to turn Jacob against me.

174
00:13:21.734 --> 00:13:22.758
It won't work.

175
00:13:28.041 --> 00:13:29.407
Bitch.

176
00:13:31.644 --> 00:13:34.478
<i>Hi. I'm Agent Parker.</i>

177
00:13:34.681 --> 00:13:36.809
We haven't officially
met. How's your hand?

178
00:13:40.553 --> 00:13:44.422
First of all. awesome
job. I'm very impressed.

179
00:13:45.158 --> 00:13:46.854
Heh. How much
planning did all this take?

180
00:13:47.794 --> 00:13:51.492
Seriously. you are
doing a great job.

181
00:13:52.865 --> 00:13:55.096
Thank you. For my book.

182
00:13:56.269 --> 00:13:57.862
You're welcome.

183
00:14:01.074 --> 00:14:04.306
Why torture critics?
That seems a little petty.

184
00:14:04.711 --> 00:14:08.478
Oh. dear. Has someone
been playing with matches?

185
00:14:09.716 --> 00:14:13.483
I like fire. sir. It started when
I was a kid and it just stuck.

186
00:14:13.686 --> 00:14:17.020
I'm not good at knives. I've
been practicing. getting better.

187
00:14:17.223 --> 00:14:18.885
But I still prefer fire.

188
00:14:19.792 --> 00:14:24.594
Definitely makes a
statement. Tell me more.

189
00:14:24.797 --> 00:14:29.997
Poe often wrote of revenge. I want
my chapter to be about revenge.

190
00:14:31.904 --> 00:14:34.738
I want to target people
who hurt you professionally.

191
00:14:36.743 --> 00:14:39.406
I've done my research.
I know who they are.

192
00:14:40.213 --> 00:14:43.877
I'm not above revenge.
agent. I think I've proved that.

193
00:14:44.050 --> 00:14:49.353
Revenge is primal. It's a universal
theme. And every good story needs one.

194
00:14:49.522 --> 00:14:51.684
Don't you agree. Ryan?

195
00:14:53.025 --> 00:14:57.190
Of course. his theme
is somewhat different.

196
00:14:57.397 --> 00:15:02.062
So your acolytes come up with ways to
make you proud with these little tributes.

197
00:15:02.368 --> 00:15:08.205
- That how they're helping write your book?
- Everyone has a story to tell. agent.

198
00:15:08.708 --> 00:15:12.839
Your little devotee. is he
gonna torch all your critics?

199
00:15:13.045 --> 00:15:16.072
There are really only three
people that I hold accountable...

200
00:15:16.249 --> 00:15:18.912
for my professional
downfall. agent.

201
00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:21.388
Isn't that right. Ryan?

202
00:15:23.022 --> 00:15:27.722
I wonder who he holds
accountable for his downfall.

203
00:15:28.394 --> 00:15:30.863
It must be very hard for you...

204
00:15:31.063 --> 00:15:35.467
<i>to be surrounded by
the stench of death again.</i>

205
00:15:36.936 --> 00:15:40.600
I know this takes a
terrible toll on you.

206
00:15:41.474 --> 00:15:44.239
<i>And you must be careful...</i>

207
00:15:45.077 --> 00:15:49.378
what with that
little heart of yours.

208
00:16:00.993 --> 00:16:02.052
What are you doing?

209
00:16:02.228 --> 00:16:05.824
Three people are responsible
for Joe's downfall. His words.

210
00:16:06.065 --> 00:16:08.057
That would be me.
the dead critic...

211
00:16:08.634 --> 00:16:09.966
and this guy.

212
00:16:10.203 --> 00:16:13.662
He was a professor at the university.
I interviewed him. He was a dean.

213
00:16:13.840 --> 00:16:18.141
After Joe's book failed. this guy denied
him tenure. Said that Joe wasn't worthy.

214
00:16:18.311 --> 00:16:21.748
It was a big blow to Joe's career.
Phillip Barnes. Dean of Literature.

215
00:16:21.948 --> 00:16:24.110
Do you think
he's still the dean?

216
00:16:24.283 --> 00:16:26.582
As far as I know.
This was years ago.

217
00:16:36.996 --> 00:16:39.431
May I help you? Did we
have an appointment?

218
00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:43.595
Why did you deny
Joe Carroll tenure?

219
00:16:45.638 --> 00:16:47.698
- I beg your pardon?
- I asked you a question.

220
00:16:47.874 --> 00:16:49.342
Is this a joke?

221
00:16:50.243 --> 00:16:52.542
I'm sorry. you
need to leave. Oh.

222
00:16:53.179 --> 00:16:54.374
No. you need to sit.

223
00:16:56.182 --> 00:16:59.448
Why did you deny
Carroll tenure? Answer me.

224
00:17:21.340 --> 00:17:24.276
I've never killed anyone
with a knife before.

225
00:17:38.558 --> 00:17:41.995
The press is using the "cult" word.
It's out there. Can you comment?

226
00:17:42.995 --> 00:17:45.157
No. let them speculate.
Where's Ryan?

227
00:17:45.665 --> 00:17:47.327
He went outside.

228
00:17:50.703 --> 00:17:53.195
There's no way you
could have stopped this.

229
00:17:53.673 --> 00:17:58.907
Yeah. I could have. You see.
that's the point. He's baiting me.

230
00:17:59.078 --> 00:18:00.546
I should have seen it coming.

231
00:18:00.713 --> 00:18:04.548
Why? Because you interviewed
him eight years ago? Seriously?

232
00:18:04.784 --> 00:18:06.582
You know Carroll's
out to torture you.

233
00:18:08.220 --> 00:18:10.052
Well. it's working.

234
00:18:24.170 --> 00:18:27.538
- Professor Carroll. Hi. I'm Ryan Hardy. FBI.
- Hmm?

235
00:18:27.740 --> 00:18:32.235
Yes. my wife said to expect you.
It's a pleasure. How can I help?

236
00:18:32.445 --> 00:18:35.210
I was hoping to pick your
brain on a case I'm working on.

237
00:18:35.381 --> 00:18:38.818
Oh. the murders. Yes.
Oh. gosh. Awful. Poor girls.

238
00:18:39.018 --> 00:18:42.887
No. I'd relish the opportunity.
I don't mean relish. I mean...

239
00:18:43.055 --> 00:18:46.890
It's not every day one gets to aid
the FBI in a murder investigation. is it?

240
00:18:47.093 --> 00:18:51.030
- Now a good time?
- I'm afraid not. I'm late for an appointment.

241
00:18:51.197 --> 00:18:54.861
But. uh. just call my office.
I'm free every night this week.

242
00:18:55.034 --> 00:18:56.434
I'll do that. Thank you. sir.

243
00:18:57.536 --> 00:19:00.938
Please. call me Joe.
Nice to meet you.

244
00:19:11.217 --> 00:19:13.686
All right. get in closer. Smile.

245
00:19:15.054 --> 00:19:17.785
- How is it?
- I don't like it. One more.

246
00:19:19.925 --> 00:19:23.919
- All right. One. two. three.
- Can I call Mom now?

247
00:19:24.230 --> 00:19:28.930
No. you cannot
and stop asking me.

248
00:19:35.941 --> 00:19:37.807
We can't pretend to be gay.

249
00:19:38.010 --> 00:19:41.913
Sarah Fuller has major issues. She's
not gonna warm up to a straight guy...

250
00:19:42.081 --> 00:19:45.176
the way she would to a totally
non-threatening gay couple.

251
00:19:45.418 --> 00:19:47.819
Yeah. I don't know.

252
00:19:48.020 --> 00:19:49.579
Joe thinks it's a great idea.

253
00:19:51.791 --> 00:19:54.351
- But we're straight.
- Details.

254
00:19:55.728 --> 00:19:58.323
Come on. Expand your minds.

255
00:19:59.932 --> 00:20:02.663
Let's try it. Kiss.

256
00:20:03.602 --> 00:20:06.162
- What. now?
- Let's see if you can pull it off.

257
00:20:09.175 --> 00:20:13.772
- No. no. No way. No way.
- You guys are losers.

258
00:20:14.680 --> 00:20:16.706
So what am I gonna tell Joe?

259
00:20:22.988 --> 00:20:29.451
Okay. okay. Let's do this.
Come on. Gay chicken.

260
00:20:58.157 --> 00:21:00.058
What's wrong with him?

261
00:21:02.695 --> 00:21:05.529
- Hey. What do you think you're doing?
- Get away.

262
00:21:05.731 --> 00:21:08.326
Come on. man. Don't do this.
And where you going. huh?

263
00:21:10.102 --> 00:21:12.582
Hey. Your face is all over the
news right now. Don't be stupid.

264
00:21:12.905 --> 00:21:14.464
You're a liar.

265
00:21:24.250 --> 00:21:29.052
<i>Authorities have yet to confirm or deny
any cult activity surrounding Joe Carroll.</i>

266
00:21:42.535 --> 00:21:44.902
So does the coffee
work as an equalizer?

267
00:21:45.604 --> 00:21:49.405
That's the idea. Got Rick
Kester's records. Just came in.

268
00:21:49.608 --> 00:21:51.406
Take a look at this.

269
00:21:53.212 --> 00:21:55.044
Wait.

270
00:21:56.649 --> 00:21:59.881
<i>A critic for the</i>
Richmond Herald <i>is dead.</i>

271
00:22:00.052 --> 00:22:02.292
<i>The assailant. a street
performer. is currently at large.</i>

272
00:22:03.522 --> 00:22:05.842
<i>- Eyewitnesses caught the image
on camera.</i> CLAIRE: Come in.

273
00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:07.793
Excuse me.

274
00:22:09.795 --> 00:22:12.629
- Claire?
- I'm watching the news. What's happening?

275
00:22:12.798 --> 00:22:15.791
<i>Listen. We have a suspect.
I need to ask you something.</i>

276
00:22:15.968 --> 00:22:18.062
- The man who's starting the fires?
<i>- Right.</i>

277
00:22:18.571 --> 00:22:21.268
I've just got his credit
card statements...

278
00:22:21.440 --> 00:22:25.138
and. uh. there's a couple of items
that I just need to confirm with you.

279
00:22:25.578 --> 00:22:31.449
All-pro sponge ball. Ridley race
car set. A Dragon Ninja warrior...

280
00:22:31.617 --> 00:22:36.419
Action figure. yeah. Those are all
Joey's favorite toys. What's going on?

281
00:22:36.622 --> 00:22:42.061
This is good news. Claire. They
bought him toys. They're not hurting him.

282
00:22:42.261 --> 00:22:45.197
I want him home. He's not
gonna be safe until he's home.

283
00:22:45.431 --> 00:22:49.198
I know. I gotta go.

284
00:22:49.435 --> 00:22:52.633
I'll call you later.
okay? Bye-bye.

285
00:22:53.105 --> 00:22:54.471
Bye.

286
00:22:56.609 --> 00:22:59.704
- I've been here all day. Can I go?
- Soon.

287
00:23:01.881 --> 00:23:05.648
Any idea why your husband
would purchase toys?

288
00:23:06.452 --> 00:23:11.152
I don't know. Uh. it's his credit
card. You'll have to ask him.

289
00:23:15.594 --> 00:23:16.687
It's Rick.

290
00:23:17.796 --> 00:23:20.095
Answer it. Put him
on speaker phone.

291
00:23:31.677 --> 00:23:32.736
Rick?

292
00:23:32.912 --> 00:23:34.608
<i>Where are you?</i>

293
00:23:35.147 --> 00:23:38.709
The FBI came to the house.
Rick. What have you done?

294
00:23:40.619 --> 00:23:43.179
<i>- Are you with them
now?</i> MAGGIE: Yes.

295
00:23:43.389 --> 00:23:46.257
Yes. They're looking for
you. Rick. You're in trouble.

296
00:23:46.492 --> 00:23:49.018
How could you hurt those people?

297
00:23:49.228 --> 00:23:50.719
<i>Where is he?</i>

298
00:23:50.896 --> 00:23:52.558
Where are you. Rick?

299
00:23:55.167 --> 00:23:57.136
<i>Is Ryan Hardy there?</i>

300
00:23:59.171 --> 00:24:01.003
<i>Tell Ryan it was all for him.</i>

301
00:24:13.919 --> 00:24:18.152
He's using the same setup as your Internet.
It's routed internationally. Can't trace it.

302
00:24:18.624 --> 00:24:21.150
What do you think? Will
he try and make contact?

303
00:24:21.727 --> 00:24:26.927
I don't know. Take her home. Stay with her.
I'll send someone to relieve in the morning.

304
00:24:27.132 --> 00:24:29.533
- I'll go with her.
- What you're gonna do...

305
00:24:29.735 --> 00:24:32.796
is go back to that motel the
FBI put us in and get some rest.

306
00:24:32.972 --> 00:24:34.668
- I'm fine. PARKER:
When's the last time...

307
00:24:34.840 --> 00:24:38.242
you had more than an hour of
sleep? Go and get some sleep. Ryan...

308
00:24:38.444 --> 00:24:41.505
and tomorrow we're gonna
find Joey. Do you understand?

309
00:24:41.747 --> 00:24:43.181
Look. I get it.

310
00:24:43.382 --> 00:24:47.615
You over-identify with the victims.
the guilt makes it personal. you unravel.

311
00:24:48.354 --> 00:24:49.378
I get it.

312
00:25:02.801 --> 00:25:04.531
You okay?

313
00:25:07.473 --> 00:25:09.806
Not going back to the
hotel to sleep. are you?

314
00:25:09.975 --> 00:25:12.376
I think Rick Kester
knows where Joey is.

315
00:25:14.313 --> 00:25:16.179
Well. they gave me a rental car.

316
00:25:21.820 --> 00:25:25.518
Joey's in his room. He
thinks we got into a little fight.

317
00:25:27.526 --> 00:25:31.190
- Paul just needed to blow off some steam.
- Our faces are all over the news.

318
00:25:32.531 --> 00:25:35.091
- And what if he goes into town?
- I know Paul.

319
00:25:35.534 --> 00:25:38.436
Okay? Heh. He's not
gonna go into town.

320
00:25:40.806 --> 00:25:44.334
- Did you send that e-mail?
- Not yet. I was waiting for Rick to call.

321
00:25:45.077 --> 00:25:47.842
Why is no one doing what
they're supposed to do?

322
00:25:48.047 --> 00:25:49.606
Damn it.

323
00:26:25.751 --> 00:26:27.879
Excuse me. Megan?

324
00:26:30.389 --> 00:26:33.359
- Where would I find the wine?
- Oh. we don't sell wine.

325
00:26:34.093 --> 00:26:36.062
All we have is
beer. It's the law.

326
00:26:36.261 --> 00:26:38.196
Well. I really wanted wine.

327
00:26:41.600 --> 00:26:43.125
Um...

328
00:26:45.737 --> 00:26:48.229
So. uh. red or white?

329
00:26:50.776 --> 00:26:52.938
Go with the red.

330
00:26:53.679 --> 00:26:56.581
And. uh. what
time do you get off?

331
00:27:10.762 --> 00:27:13.425
Do you really think
he's gonna come here?

332
00:27:15.467 --> 00:27:18.198
We just want to keep
you safe. that's all.

333
00:27:19.771 --> 00:27:22.263
Do what you normally do.
Pretend I'm not even here.

334
00:27:22.441 --> 00:27:23.932
Uh...

335
00:27:24.109 --> 00:27:26.044
Help yourself to the fridge.

336
00:27:31.283 --> 00:27:33.980
- Yo.
- Hardy and I are outside.

337
00:27:34.153 --> 00:27:36.850
<i>What? Does Parker know?</i>

338
00:27:38.357 --> 00:27:39.655
Yeah.

339
00:27:43.996 --> 00:27:47.933
Do you really think Kester would
be stupid enough to come here?

340
00:27:48.200 --> 00:27:49.691
<i>He's killed two people today.</i>

341
00:27:50.569 --> 00:27:54.301
He's escalating. he's getting
bolder. Be outside if you need us.

342
00:27:54.973 --> 00:27:56.464
Yeah.

343
00:27:59.945 --> 00:28:01.243
Does Parker know we're here?

344
00:28:03.315 --> 00:28:05.250
She told me to watch you.

345
00:28:07.085 --> 00:28:10.749
Look. I know you march to your own
drum and everything and that's cool.

346
00:28:10.956 --> 00:28:11.980
Maybe someday I can...

347
00:28:12.157 --> 00:28:16.094
but I'm the second-youngest agent in
the BAU and people still look at me funny.

348
00:28:17.963 --> 00:28:19.898
This is my career. sir.

349
00:28:24.369 --> 00:28:26.736
- You still live in Brooklyn?
- Yeah.

350
00:28:27.372 --> 00:28:29.273
You ever make it up to Albany?

351
00:28:29.474 --> 00:28:31.602
I read your book. I
know you grew up there.

352
00:28:32.911 --> 00:28:35.403
Not for years.
There's no reason.

353
00:28:37.416 --> 00:28:38.907
Right.

354
00:28:39.518 --> 00:28:40.850
Your family...

355
00:28:41.920 --> 00:28:45.015
Sorry. Um. I'm a military brat.

356
00:28:45.257 --> 00:28:49.922
- Born in San Diego. I've lived everywhere...
- I'm gonna look around. stretch my legs.

357
00:29:04.810 --> 00:29:06.608
Ryan. good to see
you. Come on in.

358
00:29:06.778 --> 00:29:09.942
I'm afraid it's only me tonight.
Claire's out with the little one.

359
00:29:10.115 --> 00:29:12.607
- Can I get you a drink?
- No. I'm fine. thanks.

360
00:29:13.385 --> 00:29:18.790
My God. This is the moment
when it all becomes very real.

361
00:29:19.825 --> 00:29:23.785
Your wife mentioned Edgar Allan
Poe as a reference for the eyes.

362
00:29:24.129 --> 00:29:27.793
What makes you think your killer
has a greater literary purpose?

363
00:29:28.033 --> 00:29:31.902
There's a sophistication to the murders.
The way the bodies were handled...

364
00:29:32.104 --> 00:29:35.939
and displayed.
There's a romance to it.

365
00:29:36.141 --> 00:29:40.078
Poe's eye allegories
would certainly fit.

366
00:29:40.912 --> 00:29:45.577
You'll find his. uh. symbolism
full of haunting romance. Here.

367
00:29:46.585 --> 00:29:49.851
Wow. great. Thanks a lot.

368
00:29:50.088 --> 00:29:53.422
- I'll get this right back to you.
- No. no. Don't you dare. This is...

369
00:29:53.592 --> 00:29:59.828
This has been a treat for me. Heh.
Now. please. may I offer you a drink?

370
00:30:03.935 --> 00:30:06.803
Heh. All right. sure. yeah.
Whatever you're drinking.

371
00:30:20.185 --> 00:30:23.451
I need a breather.
And more wine.

372
00:30:26.124 --> 00:30:27.683
Sure.

373
00:30:32.664 --> 00:30:36.032
We're not having sex. okay?
Let's just take that off the table.

374
00:30:36.635 --> 00:30:37.864
Okay.

375
00:30:46.645 --> 00:30:49.547
Oh. my God. that hurt.
Were you just choking me?

376
00:30:49.748 --> 00:30:52.809
No. No. of course not.

377
00:30:53.251 --> 00:30:55.243
We should get
going. It's getting late.

378
00:30:55.487 --> 00:30:57.979
- But...
- I need to get home.

379
00:30:59.491 --> 00:31:00.789
Okay.

380
00:31:02.160 --> 00:31:03.321
Okay.

381
00:31:06.565 --> 00:31:08.227
Wait. Let me get
the door for you.

382
00:31:26.051 --> 00:31:27.713
Don't be so happy to see me.

383
00:31:27.919 --> 00:31:29.251
Will you excuse us. please?

384
00:31:35.327 --> 00:31:36.727
I'm not talking to you.

385
00:31:37.195 --> 00:31:40.461
Well. you're gonna have to. I need
some information from you. Jordy.

386
00:31:41.733 --> 00:31:43.634
<i>Believe it or not
I'm walking on air</i>

387
00:31:43.802 --> 00:31:45.065
So I was talking to Joe...

388
00:31:47.639 --> 00:31:49.403
and he wants to see you.

389
00:31:51.643 --> 00:31:52.906
I wanna see him.

390
00:31:53.578 --> 00:31:56.742
I can make that happen. But
I can't if you won't talk to me.

391
00:32:02.721 --> 00:32:03.780
You okay in here?

392
00:32:04.756 --> 00:32:05.917
Yeah. I guess.

393
00:32:09.027 --> 00:32:11.292
Are you married. Agent Riley?

394
00:32:11.763 --> 00:32:13.459
Divorced.

395
00:32:15.000 --> 00:32:16.525
Was she a good woman?

396
00:32:17.969 --> 00:32:19.096
She wasn't the problem.

397
00:32:23.742 --> 00:32:25.233
What was that?

398
00:32:30.549 --> 00:32:32.245
Was that inside or outside?

399
00:33:09.154 --> 00:33:10.816
- Yeah.
- You okay?

400
00:33:10.989 --> 00:33:14.289
I'm not sure. There's
someone in the backyard.

401
00:33:15.327 --> 00:33:16.351
I'm coming in.

402
00:33:16.528 --> 00:33:18.156
How do I know you're not lying?

403
00:33:18.363 --> 00:33:20.923
What if I tell you stuff and
you don't let me see Joe?

404
00:33:21.099 --> 00:33:24.558
Character. Jordy. I say what
I mean and I mean what I say.

405
00:33:24.803 --> 00:33:27.602
If you don't like the stuff I
tell you do I get to see Joe?

406
00:33:27.839 --> 00:33:30.934
Just talk to me. Jordy.
I'll let you see Joe.

407
00:33:32.043 --> 00:33:33.568
I don't know where the kid is.

408
00:33:33.812 --> 00:33:35.906
- Oh. come on. Jordy...
- I don't.

409
00:33:36.581 --> 00:33:39.415
We divide the secrets so no
one person knows everything...

410
00:33:39.584 --> 00:33:41.212
in case one of us gets caught.

411
00:33:42.621 --> 00:33:43.680
So who has Joey?

412
00:33:43.855 --> 00:33:47.690
Emma and Jacob and Paul. But I don't
know where they are and that's the truth.

413
00:33:47.893 --> 00:33:49.259
Can I see Joe now?

414
00:33:49.461 --> 00:33:52.061
- Does Rick know where Joey is?
- I don't know. But his wife does.

415
00:33:52.097 --> 00:33:53.326
- What?
- Maggie.

416
00:33:53.532 --> 00:33:55.558
She and Emma planned that part.

417
00:34:01.273 --> 00:34:04.209
Something's up. Hello.

418
00:34:04.943 --> 00:34:06.536
- You lied!
- It's Parker.

419
00:34:06.745 --> 00:34:09.943
Jordy just told me Maggie
Kester is one of them. She's lying.

420
00:34:10.415 --> 00:34:11.439
Maggie is one of them.

421
00:34:16.588 --> 00:34:19.353
Maggie. You're
getting a message.

422
00:34:19.558 --> 00:34:20.753
What does it say?

423
00:34:20.926 --> 00:34:22.417
It says:

424
00:34:22.594 --> 00:34:24.119
"Now."

425
00:34:24.930 --> 00:34:26.228
What the...?

426
00:34:49.087 --> 00:34:50.887
- Are you okay?
- You went too deep.

427
00:34:50.922 --> 00:34:53.949
Oh. my God. I'm so sorry.
- You lose.

428
00:34:54.159 --> 00:34:56.754
- You suck at games.
- He sucks at knives.

429
00:34:56.928 --> 00:35:00.126
- All right. who's next? Truth or dare.
- Guys. she needs a hospital.

430
00:35:00.332 --> 00:35:02.631
- What?
- Oh. my God. baby. I'm so sorry.

431
00:35:02.801 --> 00:35:03.996
Baby. I'm so sorry.

432
00:35:04.936 --> 00:35:07.030
There's no time. We have to go.

433
00:35:16.181 --> 00:35:17.547
Get an ambulance.

434
00:35:19.985 --> 00:35:23.854
- Here. Hold pressure on this.
- Okay. okay. Hold on. I got it.

435
00:35:24.823 --> 00:35:27.691
Hey. Troy. Look at
me. You'll be okay.

436
00:35:27.926 --> 00:35:30.862
Stop. Stop.

437
00:35:31.062 --> 00:35:34.328
Please. Please.
he's gonna kill me.

438
00:35:35.533 --> 00:35:36.933
I don't think so. Maggie.

439
00:35:42.841 --> 00:35:44.207
No!

440
00:36:31.389 --> 00:36:33.119
What is that?

441
00:36:36.094 --> 00:36:37.460
What the hell?

442
00:36:39.097 --> 00:36:44.126
Hey. guys. this is Megan.
Megan. this is Emma and Jacob.

443
00:36:44.335 --> 00:36:45.803
- Who is she?
- She's a friend.

444
00:36:46.971 --> 00:36:49.270
And she's gonna be
staying with us for a while.

445
00:36:50.475 --> 00:36:51.841
You have lost your mind.

446
00:36:52.977 --> 00:36:57.813
- I'm done listening to her.
- Hey. I'll take care of this.

447
00:36:58.049 --> 00:36:59.813
Go check on Joey.

448
00:37:01.786 --> 00:37:02.810
Go.

449
00:37:10.628 --> 00:37:14.292
- What are you doing. Paul?
- I'm tired of being the third wheel.

450
00:37:14.466 --> 00:37:15.490
And now I'm not.

451
00:37:17.168 --> 00:37:21.629
I know you're mad at me right now
but you can't ruin things for everyone.

452
00:37:21.840 --> 00:37:24.833
Does Emma know
what a liar you are?

453
00:37:26.111 --> 00:37:28.671
We promised we
wouldn't tell anyone.

454
00:37:31.082 --> 00:37:32.106
Especially Emma.

455
00:37:35.120 --> 00:37:37.419
I drank too much. Sarah's
gonna think I'm a drunk.

456
00:37:37.589 --> 00:37:43.358
- Are you kidding? She loves you.
- You had a few too many too. you know that?

457
00:37:43.528 --> 00:37:45.724
You are so touchy-feely
when you drink.

458
00:37:45.964 --> 00:37:47.398
- Hey. it's for Sarah.
- Mm-hm.

459
00:37:47.632 --> 00:37:50.295
- We gotta look like a real couple.
- Oh. touchy...

460
00:37:50.468 --> 00:37:51.663
Heh-heh. Stop that.

461
00:38:15.560 --> 00:38:17.256
All right. look.

462
00:38:19.697 --> 00:38:20.824
We can't keep her here.

463
00:38:21.733 --> 00:38:25.534
Look. I'll help you take her
into the basement. Okay?

464
00:38:50.061 --> 00:38:53.554
That woman fooled
me today and I am...

465
00:38:53.731 --> 00:38:54.858
mad.

466
00:38:56.434 --> 00:38:58.096
Riley didn't have to die.

467
00:39:06.211 --> 00:39:08.976
Thanks a lot. I'll read
it right away. I promise.

468
00:39:09.280 --> 00:39:12.444
Feel free to hate it.
Everyone else has. Heh.

469
00:39:12.617 --> 00:39:13.744
It's not doing well?

470
00:39:13.918 --> 00:39:17.719
- I think that's the third copy.
- I should give you 20 bucks or something.

471
00:39:19.257 --> 00:39:25.254
- Listen. I really appreciate tonight. Joe.
- If nothing else. it's good scotch.

472
00:39:25.463 --> 00:39:27.193
- It's great scotch.
- Hmm.

473
00:39:27.999 --> 00:39:30.901
You know. I've been working
on this case nonstop for months.

474
00:39:31.469 --> 00:39:36.999
Sometimes I just forget to stop
and turn it off for a few hours.

475
00:39:37.475 --> 00:39:39.967
I couldn't turn it
off if I were you.

476
00:39:40.979 --> 00:39:44.108
Must be hard with
friends and family...

477
00:39:44.282 --> 00:39:48.117
when you're running around
trying to chase down the bad guy.

478
00:39:48.953 --> 00:39:53.118
I imagine it. uh.
gets quite lonely.

479
00:39:57.095 --> 00:39:59.291
But the payoff. ah? Heh.

480
00:39:59.998 --> 00:40:02.934
You're helping
people. Saving lives.

481
00:40:05.036 --> 00:40:08.234
Yeah. I think what you do...

482
00:40:09.040 --> 00:40:12.101
is quite remarkable.

483
00:40:16.648 --> 00:40:17.809
One more. huh?

484
00:40:20.118 --> 00:40:21.245
Sure. why not.

485
00:40:25.790 --> 00:40:26.883
Joe fooled me.

486
00:40:29.260 --> 00:40:33.129
I should've known the first time I met
him he was the man I was looking for.

487
00:40:33.364 --> 00:40:34.889
He had this power.

488
00:40:35.767 --> 00:40:37.531
I'm sorry. Joe.

489
00:40:38.002 --> 00:40:40.028
I'm sorry. Joe!

490
00:40:42.040 --> 00:40:45.499
Charm and seduce.

491
00:40:46.144 --> 00:40:47.840
I know what his followers feel.

492
00:41:01.826 --> 00:41:03.658
They're better for
being near him.

493
00:41:05.663 --> 00:41:10.294
He knows how to give them a
little piece of what they're missing.

494
00:41:21.546 --> 00:41:22.844
I fell for it.

495
00:41:31.356 --> 00:41:33.257
And five more girls
were murdered.

496
00:41:50.074 --> 00:41:51.565
I got your message. What is it?

497
00:41:53.077 --> 00:41:54.943
I got an e-mail.

498
00:42:01.119 --> 00:42:04.453
<i>See. if you catch the sun
just right. the bug catches fire.</i>

499
00:42:04.655 --> 00:42:06.214
<i>Why do you wanna kill a bug?</i>

500
00:42:07.358 --> 00:42:08.951
<i>Because we can.</i>

501
00:42:09.127 --> 00:42:13.997
<i>See. if you kill the bug. then it
dies. And your life means a little more.</i>

502
00:42:15.166 --> 00:42:17.761
<i>- I don't understand.
- Look at this little guy.</i>

503
00:42:17.969 --> 00:42:21.269
<i>- Where did you get a cute little mouse?
- Caught him in a trap.</i>

504
00:42:21.439 --> 00:42:23.999
<i>Here. screw the lid on.
It's gotta be real tight.</i>

505
00:42:24.175 --> 00:42:27.168
<i>- Then it's gonna suffocate.
It will die.</i> JACOB: <i>Exactly.</i>

506
00:42:27.378 --> 00:42:30.143
<i>- Here. Screw the lid on.
- I don't want to.</i>

507
00:42:30.381 --> 00:42:32.111
<i>It's okay. sweetie. Go ahead.</i>

508
00:42:33.885 --> 00:42:35.751
<i>Then we watch it
go straight to heaven.</i>

509
00:42:35.953 --> 00:42:38.184
<i>- There you go.
- Good. Joey.</i>

510
00:42:39.257 --> 00:42:42.091
<i>- I've never killed anything
before.</i> JACOB: <i>Heh.</i>

511
00:42:42.260 --> 00:42:44.422
<i>We're just getting started.</i>

512
00:42:44.629 --> 00:42:45.688
They're teaching him.

513
00:42:46.497 --> 00:42:51.800
- Claire. We're going to find him.
- Then do it.

514
00:42:52.003 --> 00:42:53.437
Claire. Claire. wait.

515
00:42:53.604 --> 00:42:56.574
<i>Joey. can you wave to the
camera and say. "Hi. Ryan"?</i>

516
00:42:56.741 --> 00:42:58.107
<i>Who's that?</i>

517
00:42:58.276 --> 00:43:00.836
<i>He's a friend. Come
on. just say it for me.</i>

518
00:43:01.012 --> 00:43:03.277
<i>Hi. Ryan.</i>
